    <h1>Roughdraft. Gist-powered writing.</h1>
  </header>

  <p>Sometimes you have something to say that's longer than a Tweet, but too small for a blog. Enter Roughdraft. The concept is simple: writing for the web, backed by <a href="https://gist.github.com">GitHub Gists</a>.</p>

  <h2 id="how_it_works">How it works</h2>

  <ol>
    <li>Create a public, <a href="http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/">Markdown</a>-formatted <a href="https://gist.github.com">Gist on Github</a> with at least one file.</li>
    <li>Note the Gist ID. Itâ€™s at the end of the URL: <code class="no-prettify">gist.github.com/jedfoster/<b>4339935</b></code>.</li>
    <li>See your Gist, made pretty, at <code>roughdraft.io/<b>gist-id</b></code></li>
  </ol>

  <h5 id="bookmarklet_steps"><b>Or</b></h5>

