  <h3 id="formatting">Formatting</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>Roughdraft uses <a href="https://help.github.com/articles/github-flavored-markdown" target="new">GitHub-flavored Markdown</a>. In addition to all of the usual Markdown syntax, GFM supports fenced code blocks and syntax highlighting.</li>
    <li>Use images and even <a href="http://www.emoji-cheat-sheet.com/" target="new">emoji</a>! <img class="emoji" title=":metal:" alt=":metal:" src="/images/emoji/metal.png" height="20" width="20" align="absmiddle"></li>
    <li>Your Gist&#8217;s <code>description</code> field will be used as the headline for your post.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>More detailed information on formatting our Gist is coming soon.</p>

  <h3 id="user_pages">User Pages</h3>

  <p>Roughdraft is built with the GitHub API, so we can do some really cool stuff, like give every GitHub user their own Roughdraft namespace!</p>

  <p>Visit <code><b>username</b>.roughdraft.io</code> to see a list of all the public, Markdown-formatted Gists belonging to <code><b>username</b></code>.</p>

